:: Coming of Age {"position":"200,275","size":"100,100"}
<img src="https://siko91.github.io/Jebe-s-Coming-Of-Age-Hunt/assets/images/1.jpg" style="max-width:80%">

The edge of the village marks the boundary between green steppe and the gray promise of the Ashen Wastelands. Fifty boys—sixteen summers old, faces painted with ritual ochre, quivers with arrows slung across their backs—stand in a wide half-circle around the shaman. Their small steppe ponies stamp and snort, sensing the tension in the air.

The shaman, old as the hills and wrapped in patched felt and eagle feathers, raises a smoking bundle of juniper and wild thyme. His voice carries low and steady over the wind:

"Spirits of the hunt watch you. The land will test your courage, your aim, your heart. Bring back the greatest prey… or do not return at all."

He walks the line, touching each boy's forehead with ash-dusted fingers, murmuring blessings in the old tongue. When he reaches Jebe, the boy straightens taller. His dark eyes are bright with hunger—not for food, but for glory. His horse, a sturdy bay mare, flicks an ear as if sharing his eagerness.

The other boys shift, some grinning fiercely, others pale and silent. Among them you spot Temur—broad-shouldered, jaw set, staring at Jebe with something colder than rivalry.

The shaman steps back. A single drumbeat echoes. Then another. The rhythm quickens.

The hunt begins.

You (the spirit) hover unseen, weightless, drawn to Jebe like smoke to flame. He does not yet know you are here… but he soon will.

