:: Minor Hazard: The Venomous Crossing {"position":"800,275","size":"100,100"}
<img src="https://siko91.github.io/Jebe-s-Coming-Of-Age-Hunt/assets/images/5.jpg" style="max-width:80%">

The trail narrows into a steep-sided gully, walls of black basalt rising sharp on either side. Ash has drifted into the bottom like dirty snow, muffling sound. Jebe slows his mare to a careful walk. Her ears flick forward, then back; she snorts once, nostrils wide.

He scans the ground. Small shapes shift in the shadows—glossy black scorpions the size of a man’s thumb, their tails curled like question marks; thin, sand-colored vipers that blend perfectly with the ash until they move. A few skitter away at the clop of hooves. Others hold their ground, pincers raised in tiny defiance.

Jebe keeps his breathing even. He loosens the reins slightly, letting the mare choose her footing. She picks her way with deliberate steps, ears swiveling, avoiding the darker patches where the creatures cluster thickest. Once she hesitates, one forehoof hovering above a coiled viper; Jebe murmurs a low word in the old tongue—half command, half reassurance—and she shifts sideways, stepping over instead of down.

A scorpion scuttles too close to her pastern. Jebe leans from the saddle and flicks his riding crop; the creature flies sideways into the rock wall with a faint crack. The mare doesn’t startle. Good girl.

Sweat prickles under his felt cap despite the chill. The gully feels like a throat closing slowly around them. Every shadow could hide fangs. Every loose stone could send a boot sliding into a nest.

He keeps his bow close across his lap, arrow nocked but not drawn. Not yet. Wasteful shots would only draw more attention.

At last the walls begin to lower. Sunlight spills in ahead, weak and gray. The mare’s stride lengthens as the path widens. Jebe exhales through his teeth, the tension in his shoulders easing a fraction.

They have crossed.

But the wasteland is still watching.

